## Background

I am using Katalon Studio, which uses Apache POI v3.17 . I&#39;m working on some sheet handlers, which are responsible for creating some random data records, handling those (into their collections), and once all is said and done, saving the data to their Spreadsheets/Sheets.

The Sheets work pretty much like database tables, as their records typically have some primary key, that is an `int`/`long`. 

## Code

Let&#39;s look at the `PracticeModelHandler`, that I am working on, which stores : 


 - `practice_id` (a `long`)
 - `practice_name` (a `String`)

```
@InheritConstructors
public class PracticeModelHandler extends BaseSheetHandler&lt;PracticeModel&gt; {

	public PracticeModel nextPracticeModel(Closure&lt;RateCardModel&gt; onCreateRateCardModel, Closure&lt;DiscountModel&gt; onCreateDiscountModel, Closure&lt;Boolean&gt; onCheckDuplicate) {
		return this.nextRecord({
			final Date startDate = SMDDateUtils.LastYear();
			final Date endDate = SMDDateUtils.GetEndDate(startDate, new ContractFactory().createWithStartDate(startDate).getContractTerm());

			PracticeModel model =  new PracticeFactory().createPracticeModel(
					&quot;Contract Renewal Test Practice - RANDOM Rate and Discount Increase ${SMDDateUtils.ToDateTimeString(new Date())}&quot;,
					startDate,
					endDate,
					{ Date start -&gt; return new ContractFactory().createWithStartDate(start) },
					onCreateRateCardModel,
					onCreateDiscountModel,
					);

			return model;
		},
		onCheckDuplicate);
	}

	public PracticeModel getPracticeModel(long npiNumber) {
		return this.usedRecords
				.find { PracticeModel model -&gt;
					return model.getNpiNumber() == npiNumber;
				}
	}

	@Override
	protected Row getRow(PracticeModel record) {
		return SMDSpreadsheetUtils.FindRowWithKey(sheet, record.getNpiNumber());
	}

	@Override
	protected String getSheetName() {
		return &quot;Practices&quot;;
	}

	@Override
	protected void setupFirstRow(Row row) {
		Cell firstColumnDescCell = row.createCell(0),
			secondColumnDescCell = row.createCell(1);

		firstColumnDescCell.setCellValue(&quot;practice_id&quot;);
		secondColumnDescCell.setCellValue(&quot;practice_name&quot;);
	}

	@Override
	protected void extractRecordFromSheet(int rowNum) {
		Row row = this.sheet.getRow(rowNum);

		this.usedRecords.push(new PracticeModel().with { PracticeModel model -&gt;
			model.setNpiNumber(row.getCell(0).getNumericCellValue().toLong());
			model.setPracticeName(row.getCell(1).getStringCellValue());

			return model;
		})
	}

	@Override
	protected void fillInRow(Row row, PracticeModel record) {
		Cell firstCell = row.getCell(0),
		secondCell = row.getCell(1);

		if (SMDSpreadsheetUtils.IsRowEmpty(row)) {
			firstCell = row.createCell(0);
			secondCell = row.createCell(1);
		}

//		firstCell.setCellValue((Long) record.getNpiNumber());
		SMDSpreadsheetUtils.WriteIntegerCellValue(firstCell, record.getNpiNumber())
		secondCell.setCellValue(record.getPracticeName());
	}
}
```

Of particular note is this `SMDSpreadsheetUtils.WriteIntegerCellValue`, which is implemented like: 

	// SOURCE: https://www.phind.com/search?cache=d4085649-039f-4d86-b5cd-963ee40bfc49
	public static void WriteIntegerCellValue(Cell cell, long value) { 
		Workbook workbook = cell.getSheet().getWorkbook();
		
		CellStyle integerStyle = workbook.createCellStyle();
		DataFormat format = workbook.createDataFormat();
		integerStyle.setDataFormat(format.getFormat(&quot;0&quot;));
		
		cell.setCellValue(value);
		cell.setCellStyle(integerStyle);
		
	}
Under the hood, on done, we copy the `Sheet` from the sheet handler to the master spreadsheet, using the following util methods: 

```
	public static Closure OnCopySheetIntoSpreadsheet(Workbook spreadsheet) {
		return { Sheet sheet -&gt;
			Sheet targetSheet = this.OnCreateIfNotExistSheet(spreadsheet)(sheet.getSheetName());

			sheet.eachWithIndex({ Row row, int rowIdx -&gt;
				row.eachWithIndex({ Cell cell, int colIdx -&gt;
					Row targetRow = targetSheet.getRow(rowIdx);
					if (targetRow == null)
						targetRow = targetSheet.createRow(rowIdx);

					Cell targetCell = targetRow.getCell(colIdx);
					if (targetCell == null)
						targetCell = targetRow.createCell(colIdx);

					this.copyCellValue(cell, targetCell);
				})
			})
		}
	}
	
	// SOURCE: ChatGPT AI
	public static void copyCellValue(Cell sourceCell, Cell targetCell) {
		switch (sourceCell.getCellType()) {
			case CellType.STRING:
				targetCell.setCellValue(sourceCell.getStringCellValue());
				break;
			case CellType.NUMERIC:
				if (DateUtil.isCellDateFormatted(sourceCell)) {
					targetCell.setCellValue(sourceCell.getDateCellValue());
				} else {
					targetCell.setCellValue(sourceCell.getNumericCellValue());
				}
				break;
			case CellType.BOOLEAN:
				targetCell.setCellValue(sourceCell.getBooleanCellValue());
				break;
			case CellType.FORMULA:
				targetCell.setCellFormula(sourceCell.getCellFormula());
				break;
			case CellType.ERROR:
				targetCell.setCellErrorValue(sourceCell.getErrorCellValue());
				break;
			case CellType.BLANK:
				targetCell.setCellValue(null);
				break;
			default:
				// If the cell type is unknown, copy the cell value as a string
				CreationHelper creationHelper = targetCell.getSheet().getWorkbook().getCreationHelper();
				targetCell.setCellValue(creationHelper.createRichTextString(sourceCell.toString()));
		}
	}
```

###

## What happens when you use this code?

On the first run, it writes the data to the Sheet. However, when I go into the spreadsheet and look at it, it looks like this: 

