To print a WebView with a print button in Kotlin using View Binding, you can follow these steps:

1. In your layout XML file, add a WebView and a Button for printing:
```
&lt;WebView
    android:id=&quot;@+id/web_view&quot;
    android:layout_width=&quot;match_parent&quot;
    android:layout_height=&quot;match_parent&quot;/&gt;

&lt;Button
    android:id=&quot;@+id/print_button&quot;
    android:layout_width=&quot;wrap_content&quot;
    android:layout_height=&quot;wrap_content&quot;
    android:text=&quot;Print&quot;/&gt;
```

2. In your activity or fragment, initialize the WebView and Button using View Binding:
```
private lateinit var binding: YourLayoutBinding

override fun onCreate(savedInstanceState: Bundle?) {
    super.onCreate(savedInstanceState)
    binding = YourLayoutBinding.inflate(layoutInflater)
    setContentView(binding.root)

    val webView = binding.webView
    val printButton = binding.printButton
    ...
}
```

3. Load your desired URL in the WebView:
```
webView.loadUrl(&quot;https://www.example.com&quot;)
```

4. Define a print function that creates a PrintManager and prints the WebView:
```
private fun printWebView() {
    val printManager = getSystemService(Context.PRINT_SERVICE) as PrintManager
    val printAdapter = webView.createPrintDocumentAdapter()
    printManager.print(&quot;Print WebView&quot;, printAdapter, PrintAttributes.Builder().build())
}
```

5. Set an OnClickListener for the print button that calls the print function:
```
printButton.setOnClickListener {
    printWebView()
}
```

Your final code should look something like this:
```
private lateinit var binding: YourLayoutBinding

override fun onCreate(savedInstanceState: Bundle?) {
    super.onCreate(savedInstanceState)
    binding = YourLayoutBinding.inflate(layoutInflater)
    setContentView(binding.root)

    val webView = binding.webView
    val printButton = binding.printButton

    webView.loadUrl(&quot;https://www.example.com&quot;)

    printButton.setOnClickListener {
        printWebView()
    }
}

private fun printWebView() {
    val printManager = getSystemService(Context.PRINT_SERVICE) as PrintManager
    val printAdapter = webView.createPrintDocumentAdapter()
    printManager.print(&quot;Print WebView&quot;, printAdapter, PrintAttributes.Builder().build())
}

